  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I want to be notified about unavailability to upgrade the application with understandable message \r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n\r\n*Summary*: It's not possible anymore to upgrade previous release version to the new one. An error appears when opening an upgraded app. We need a friendly informative message asking a user to reinstall the app\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nPop up with asking to uninstall and install the app appears\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nError `com.facebook.react.commonException...` pop up appears\r\n<img width=\"330\" alt=\"aa\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29711298/38696797-e362a4b8-3e98-11e8-9d9a-363cfed2726a.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Install Status app release 0.9.16 version (from Play Store or from the [link](http://artifacts.status.im:8081/artifactory/nightlies-local/im.status.ethereum-28ec8a.apk))\r\n- Upgrade the application to the latest develop build ([link](http://artifacts.status.im:8081/artifactory/nightlies-local/im.status.ethereum-714873.apk))\r\n\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n- Notify a user that the app couldn't be upgraded and should be uninstalled first in the Play Store description\r\n- Create information message instead of error pop up to be appeared in case if a user has updated the app already\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: [apk](http://artifacts.status.im:8081/artifactory/nightlies-local/im.status.ethereum-714873.apk)\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
